{"type":"message","id":"d4982a3e","parentId":"ff6edab7","timestamp":"2026-03-17T03:28:22.506Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f10a2678e785479a97ef3919","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Detailed Concept Prompts for CESM-Diff\n\n## Fig.1 - Overall Architecture (双栏宽幅)\n\nA detailed, high-resolution scientific flowchart illustrating the CLIP-Enhanced Semantic Manifold Diffusion (CESM-Diff) framework for zero-shot fault diagnosis, presented in IEEE TIM journal style. The diagram is divided into three horizontally-arranged main sections.\n\n**Section 1: Semantic Encoding (Left, Light Blue Background)**\n\nThe process begins with a set of three rounded boxes at the top, each containing natural language fault descriptions (dashed border, deep blue #2E86AB):\n- Box 1: \"Bearing wear, high-frequency periodic impacts\"\n- Box 2: \"Valve sticking, slow drift in response\"\n- Box 3: \"Thermal instability, pressure surge\"\n\nStraight arrows point downward from each text box to a unified cyan rounded rectangle labeled \"CLIP Text Encoder\" (solid border, #00ACC1). The encoder is depicted as a Transformer architecture with 12 layers, showing internal self-attention mechanism icons.\n\nBelow the CLIP encoder, three output arrows lead to feature bars labeled \"Semantic Embeddings\" (gradient colors from blue to purple), each with dimension labels \"s₁,\" \"s₂,\" \"s₃\" representing 512-dimensional vectors on a unit hypersphere.\n\nTo the right of this section, a small annotation box shows the mathematical formula: \"s_c = E_text(Prompt_c) / ||E_text(Prompt_c)||₂\"\n\n**Section 2: Dual-Path Semantic Diffusion (Center, Light Purple Background)**\n\nThis is the core of the diagram, showing two parallel vertical pipelines:\n\n**Feature Path (Upper, Blue tones #2E86AB → #A23B58):**\n- A rounded box at the top labeled \"Noisy Features x_T\" with a random dot pattern icon inside (representing Gaussian noise)\n- A vertical sequence of 4 rounded rectangles representing denoising steps, labeled \"t=T\", \"t=T-1\", \"t=T-2\", \"t=1\"\n- Each rectangle shows progressively cleaner feature representations (from random dots to organized shapes)\n- Skip connections (curved arrows) connect corresponding encoder-decoder levels\n\n**Semantic Path (Lower, Purple tones #7B2CBF → #9D4EDD):**\n- A rounded box at the top labeled \"Noisy Semantic s_t\" with gradient pattern\n- A vertical sequence of 4 rounded rectangles showing semantic refinement steps\n- Each step shows the semantic vector being progressively denoised\n\n**Cross-Path Attention (Center junction):**\n- Bidirectional curved arrows between Feature Path and Semantic Path at each denoising layer\n- Small attention weight icons (heatmap matrices) at each connection point\n- Label: \"Cross-Path Attention (CPA)\" with mathematical notation: \"Q = W_q H_x, K = W_k H_s\"\n\nAt the bottom of this section, a horizontal block labeled \"Reverse Diffusion Process\" shows the iteration from t=T to t=0, with arrow pointing to the output.\n\n**Section 3: Feature Generation and Classification (Right, Light Green Background)**\n\nThe output from the Feature Path flows into a yellow rounded rectangle labeled \"Generated Fault Features x̂_0\" showing clean feature representations.\n\nTwo parallel flows emerge:\n- Upper flow: Arrow to a rounded box \"Feature Concatenation\" (dashed border)\n- Lower flow: Arrow from Semantic Path showing final semantic embedding s_0\n\nBoth flows merge into a scatter plot diagram labeled \"Discriminative Feature Space\" showing:\n- Dense clusters for seen classes (blue circles)\n- Semi-transparent clusters for unseen classes (orange diamonds)\n- Clear separation boundaries between clusters\n\nFrom the feature space, arrows point to a trapezoidal block labeled \"Classifier\" (Softmax/SVM), which outputs to three final boxes:\n- \"Seen Fault Diagnosis\" (checkmark icon)\n- \"Unseen Fault Diagnosis\" (star icon)\n- \"Generalized Diagnosis\" (dual icon)\n\n**Style Notes:**\n- Background: White with subtle section dividers\n- Color scheme: Blue (#2E86AB) for feature processing, Purple (#7B2CBF) for semantic processing, Green (#4CAF50) for output\n- Use clean rectangular and rounded shapes throughout\n- Arrows: Dark gray (#333333) with arrowheads, 2px stroke\n- Text labels: Arial font, black, professional sizing\n- Add subtle drop shadows for depth (optional)\n- IEEE style: Clean, professional, no excessive gradients or 3D effects\n- Important: Do not write any width scale (px) or font size (pt) in the figure.\n\n---\n\n## Fig.2 - Semantic Manifold Interpolation (单栏)\n\nA detailed 2D visualization showing the Semantic Manifold Interpolation (SMI) concept for zero-shot fault diagnosis, in IEEE journal style.\n\n**Axes:**\n- X-axis: \"Semantic Dimension 1\" with tick marks and grid lines\n- Y-axis: \"Semantic Dimension 2\" with tick marks and grid lines\n- Both axes in black, 1px line weight\n\n**Manifold Representation:**\n\nThe hypersphere surface is projected onto 2D as concentric circles, with the center representing the origin.\n\n**Seen Classes (Solid Markers):**\n- Three large filled circles representing seen fault classes:\n  - Circle 1 (Blue #2171B5): \"Fault Class A - Bearing Wear\" at upper-left position\n  - Circle 2 (Green #4DAF4A): \"Fault Class B - Valve Degradation\" at center-right position  \n  - Circle 3 (Orange #FF7F00): \"Fault Class C - Thermal Anomaly\" at lower-center position\n- Each circle has a label inside or adjacent to it\n- Circle sizes: 20px diameter equivalent\n\n**Unseen Classes (Hollow Markers):**\n- Three hollow diamond shapes representing unseen classes:\n  - Diamond 1: Positioned between Class A and Class B\n  - Diamond 2: Positioned between Class B and Class C\n  - Diamond 3: Positioned between Class A and Class C\n- Diamond size: 16px diagonal equivalent\n- Fill: White with 2px colored stroke matching the nearest seen class\n\n**Interpolation Visualization:**\n- Curved dashed lines (gray #999, 1px dashed) connecting each pair of seen class centers\n- Along each dashed line, show 3 small intermediate markers (small circles, 8px) representing interpolated semantic points at γ = 0.25, 0.5, 0.75\n- These intermediate points show gradient fill from the color of one seen class to another\n\n**Gradient Region:**\n- Light gradient shaded area (light blue #DEEBF7 to white) covering the triangular region formed by the three seen classes\n- This represents the continuous semantic manifold where interpolation is valid\n\n**Slerp Formula Annotation:**\n- A text box in the upper-right corner shows the mathematical formula:\n  - \"Slerp(s_A, s_B, γ) = sin((1-γ)Ω)/sin(Ω) · s_A + sin(γΩ)/sin(Ω) · s_B\"\n  - Where Ω = arccos(s_A · s_B)\n\n**Legend:**\n- Small legend box in lower-right corner with:\n  - Solid circle: Seen classes\n  - Hollow diamond: Unseen classes\n  - Dashed line: Interpolation path\n\n**Style Notes:**\n- Background: White (#FFFFFF)\n- Grid: Light gray (#E0E0E0) subtle grid lines\n- Axes: Black (#000000), 1.5px, with tick marks\n- Font: Arial, 10pt for labels, 8pt for annotations\n- Important: Do not write any dimensions or font sizes in the figure.\n\n---\n\n## Fig.3 - Dual-Path Denoising Process (单栏)\n\nA comprehensive diagram showing the Dual-Path Denoising Process in the diffusion model for fault diagnosis, IEEE style. The diagram flows vertically from top (noisy input) to bottom (clean output).\n\n**Layout: Two parallel columns representing the Feature Path and Semantic Path**\n\n**Top Section (t = T, Pure Noise):**\n- A unified header bar labeled \"t = T (Initial Noise)\" with light gray background\n- Left column: A large rounded rectangle filled with random dot pattern (representing Gaussian noise), labeled \"x_T: Noisy Feature Vector\"\n- Right column: A large rounded rectangle with gradient noise pattern, labeled \"s_T: Noisy Semantic Vector\"\n- Both rectangles have dimension labels: \"d_x = 256\" and \"d_s = 512\"\n\n**Middle Section (Denoising Steps t = T-1 to t = 1):**\nFour horizontal rows, each representing one denoising step:\n\n**Row 1 (t = T-1):**\n- Left column (Feature): Rounded rectangle with noisy-dot pattern but slightly more organized, labeled \"Feature Denoising Block\"\n- Right column (Semantic): Rounded rectangle with noisy gradient but slightly cleaner, labeled \"Semantic Refinement Block\"\n- Center: Curved bidirectional arrow connecting the two blocks, labeled \"Cross-Path Attention\"\n- Small icon above the arrow showing attention weight matrix (3×3 heatmap)\n\n**Row 2 (t = T-k):**\n- Left column: Rounded rectangle with semi-organized pattern showing emerging structure\n- Right column: Rounded rectangle with cleaner gradient\n- Center: Another Cross-Path Attention connection\n- Add small text labels: \"Query: H_x\" \"Key/Value: H_s\"\n\n**Row 3 (t = T-m):**\n- Left column: Rounded rectangle with mostly organized features, some residual noise dots\n- Right column: Rounded rectangle with nearly clean semantic vector\n- Center: Cross-Path Attention with label \"Conditioning semantic information into feature space\"\n\n**Row 4 (t = 1):**\n- Left column: Nearly clean feature representation, mostly solid shapes\n- Right column: Nearly clean semantic vector\n- Center: Final Cross-Path Attention connection\n\n**Bottom Section (t = 0, Clean Output):**\n- Unified header bar labeled \"t = 0 (Denoised Output)\" with light green background (#E8F5E9)\n- Left column: Clean, organized feature block labeled \"x̂_0: Generated Feature\" with solid geometric shapes inside\n- Right column: Clean semantic vector labeled \"ŝ_0: Final Semantic Embedding\" with smooth gradient\n- Center: A horizontal arrow pointing right into a fusion icon\n\n**Feature Fusion (Bottom):**\n- A rounded rectangle labeled \"Feature Concatenation [x̂_0 || ŝ_0]\"\n- Arrow pointing to a final rounded rectangle labeled \"Discriminative Feature for Classification\"\n\n**Color Scheme:**\n- Feature Path: Blue gradient from #2E86AB (top) to #A23B58 (bottom), representing progressive denoising\n- Semantic Path: Purple gradient from #7B2CBF (top) to #9D4EDD (bottom)\n- Cross-Path Attention: Orange (#FF9800) accent arrows\n- Noise representation: Random dot patterns with varying density\n- Clean features: Solid shapes with smooth edges\n\n**Arrow Annotations:**\n- Large downward arrow on the left side labeled \"Forward Diffusion\" with faded dashed style\n- Large downward arrow on the right side labeled \"Reverse Diffusion\" with solid style\n\n**Style Notes:**\n- Background: White\n- Use consistent rounded rectangles (8px corner radius)\n- Arrows: Dark gray (#333333), 2px, with filled arrowheads\n- Text labels: Arial, professional sizing\n- Add subtle box shadows for depth\n- Important: Do not write any dimensions or font sizes in the figure.\n\n---\n\n## Fig.4 - Training Pipeline Overview (单栏)\n\nA detailed flowchart showing the complete training pipeline of CESM-Diff, presented in IEEE journal style. The diagram is organized in a horizontal flow from left to right.\n\n**Stage 1: Data Preparation (Left Section, Light Orange Background)**\n\nAt the far left, three input sources:\n- A cylinder icon labeled \"Raw Sensor Data\" (vibration/acoustic signals)\n- A document icon labeled \"Fault Descriptions\" (text prompts)\n- A database icon labeled \"Class Labels\" (seen/unseen split)\n\nArrows from each converge to a processing block:\n- A trapezoid block labeled \"1D-CNN / ResNet Encoder\" producing feature vectors\n- A separate arrow points to \"CLIP Text Encoder\" producing semantic embeddings\n\nOutput: Two parallel streams labeled \"Features x ∈ ℝ^d\" and \"Semantic s ∈ ℝ^k\"\n\n**Stage 2: Pre-training (Center-Left Section, Light Yellow Background)**\n\nTwo parallel pre-training modules:\n\nModule A: \"Attribute Regressor Pre-training\"\n- Arrow from Features to a neural network block labeled \"Regressor R(·)\"\n- Arrow from Semantic embeddings to the same regressor\n- Output: Trained regressor with checkmark icon\n- Annotation: \"L_R = ||R(x) - s||²\"\n\nModule B: \"Semantic Encoding Validation\"\n- Arrow from Text Descriptions to CLIP encoder\n- Output: Semantic embeddings with validation checkmark\n- Annotation: \"s_c = normalized(E_text(Prompt_c))\"\n\n**Stage 3: Dual-Path Diffusion Training (Center Section, Light Blue Background)**\n\nThis is the main training loop, shown as a cyclic process:\n\nInput arrows from both Features and Semantic embeddings converge:\n- Both inputs go through \"Forward Diffusion\" blocks (parallel)\n  - Feature path: x_t = √(ᾱ_t)x_0 + √(1-ᾱ_t)ε\n  - Semantic path: s_t = √(ᾱ_t^s)s_0 + √(1-ᾱ_t^s)ε^s\n\nThe noisy inputs enter the \"DPSD Network\" block (main rectangle):\n- Inside show two parallel processing streams with cross-attention connections\n- Label: \"U-Net with Cross-Path Attention\"\n\nThree output arrows from the network:\n- Arrow 1: \"Predicted Noise ε_θ\" → \"Diffusion Loss L_diff\"\n- Arrow 2: Through pre-trained Regressor → \"Attribute Consistency Loss L_ACL\"\n- Arrow 3: Through interpolation module → \"SMI Loss L_SMI\"\n\nAll losses combine into \"Total Loss L_total = L_diff + ηL_ACL + σL_SMI\"\n\n**Stage 4: Inference / Generation (Right Section, Light Green Background)**\n\nFinal generation process:\n- Input: \"New Fault Description (Unseen Class)\" text box\n- Arrow to \"CLIP Encoder\" producing semantic s_u\n- Arrow to \"DDIM Sampler (50 steps)\" block with the trained DPSD\n- Arrow to \"Generated Features x̂_u\" output block\n- Arrow to \"Classifier Training\" block\n- Final output: \"Zero-Shot Diagnosis Results\"\n\n**Style Notes:**\n- Use consistent color coding across stages\n- Add mathematical formulas in annotation boxes\n- Show the iterative nature of training with curved return arrow\n- Clean, professional IEEE style throughout\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773718102504}}
