ult attribute transfer and the attribute transfer under the multi-Gaussian assumption to attain better attribute transfer ability</strong>...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d5d51b996199d417\">>>","published":"October 7, 2023","siteName":"www.sciencedirect.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"27d596246a28d277\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nZero-Shot Rolling Bearing Fault Diagnosis Based on Attribute Description\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"27d596246a28d277\">>>","url":"https://www.mdpi.com/2079-9292/14/3/452","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"500398863f4423cc\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nTo address these challenges, a ... is proposed, which <strong>realizes knowledge transfer from seen to unseen categories by constructing attribute information, thereby reducing the dependence on labeled samples</strong>....\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"500398863f4423cc\">>>","published":"January 23, 2025","siteName":"www.mdpi.com"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773721334181}}
{"type":"message","id":"93caa204","parentId":"899dff6d","timestamp":"2026-03-17T04:22:15.432Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ed968217cb084555a7316e4b","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"CLIP zero-shot fault diagnosis diffusion model\",\n  \"provider\": \"brave\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1247,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"brave\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fd1daa8311bee5d3\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGeneralized Zero-Shot Learning Based on Diffusion Model and Multilabel Network for Compound Fault Diagnosis | IEEE Journals & Magazine | IEEE Xplore\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fd1daa8311bee5d3\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/11017372/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"25ac1e1ef0f6dc1d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nExisting zero-shot compound fault diagnosis methods <strong>lack the ability to simultaneously recognize both seen and unseen fault classes</strong>, especially when aligning attributes of unseen faults, where a dimensionality ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"25ac1e1ef0f6dc1d\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"ieeexplore.ieee.org\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f05626cbfa892fc5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nZero-shot fault diagnosis using soft semantic embedding of diffusion-encoded probability - ScienceDirect\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f05626cbfa892fc5\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S1474034625002125\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0f6b2bf6e5da0028\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n<strong>A diffusion-encoded convolutional autoencoder is first trained on abundant normal data to extract features for capturing essential fault patterns from raw data</strong>. A soft semantic learning network is then constructed using a Gaussian mixture model ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0f6b2bf6e5da0028\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"April 15, 2025\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.sciencedirect.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ee6be4780fe20840\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nCLIP Meets Diffusion: A Synergistic Approach to Anomaly Detection\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ee6be4780fe20840\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://arxiv.org/html/2506.11772v1\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9235309b4401fc76\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nWe propose CLIPFUSION (= CLIP + ... and diffusion) approaches. In the zero-shot scenario, <strong>CLIPFUSION effectively identifies anomalies by integrating image-text alignment from a CLIP-based model and cross-attention maps</strong> [7, 55, 33] from a diffusion-based model....\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9235309b4401fc76\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"June 13, 2025\",\n      \"siteName\": \"arxiv.org\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0f2d7d4ef64be1e6\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGitHub - M-3LAB/awesome-industrial-anomaly-detection: Paper list and datasets for industrial image anomaly/defect detection (updating). 工业异常/瑕疵检测论文及数据集检索库(持续更新)。\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0f2d7d4ef64be1e6\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/M-3LAB/awesome-industrial-anomaly-detection\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f5fa2689184c9a16\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBayesian Prompt Flow Learning for Zero-Shot Anomaly Detection [CVPR 2025][code coming soon] DefectFill: Realistic Defect Generation with Inpainting Diffusion Model for Visual Inspection [CVPR 2025]\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f5fa2689184c9a16\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0e24ed747a0d0cbe\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nIdentifying and Mitigating Model Failures through Few-shot CLIP-aided Diffusion Generation\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0e24ed747a0d0cbe\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://arxiv.org/html/2312.05464v1\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b9c7f865887d3b02\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nWe then pinpoint spurious correlations, ... can appear in?&quot; and remove redundacies after obtaining all uncommon backgrounds. Subsequently, a zero-shot classification using CLIP <strong>identifies the background for each failure among all the uncommon backgrounds</strong>....\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b9c7f865887d3b02\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"December 9, 2023\",\n      \"siteName\": \"arxiv.org\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"CLIP zero-shot fault diagnosis diffusion model","provider":"brave","count":5,"tookMs":1247,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"brave","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fd1daa8311bee5d3\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nGeneralized Zero-Shot Learning Based on Diffusion Model and Multilabel Network for Compound Fault Diagnosis | IEEE Journals & Magazine | IEEE Xplore\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fd1daa8311bee5d3\">>>","url":"https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/11017372/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"25ac1e1ef0f6dc1d\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nExisting zero-shot compound fault diagnosis methods <strong>lack the ability to simultaneously recognize both seen and unseen fault classes</strong>, especially when aligning attributes of unseen faults, where a dimensionality ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"25ac1e1ef0f6dc1d\">>>","siteName":"ieeexplore.ieee.org"},{"title":"\