{"type":"message","id":"98f4b3d7","parentId":"069f3248","timestamp":"2026-03-17T04:22:26.077Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_88ec24dd8dc94a9cb859722f","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"DP-CDDPM-AC dual path conditional diffusion fault diagnosis\",\n  \"provider\": \"brave\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1414,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"brave\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"abfa9174dd07450c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nA fault diagnosis method based on an improved diffusion model under limited sample conditions | PLOS One\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"abfa9174dd07450c\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0309714\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2944e72201b525fa\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nIn the process of inverse diffusion, if we give xt and x0, we can calculate xt-1 based on the posterior diffusion conditional probability. (7) According to the properties of the Gaussian distribution and Formula (1), it can be concluded that (8)\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2944e72201b525fa\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"September 3, 2024\",\n      \"siteName\": \"journals.plos.org\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6810a6a3fa386e7e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nA global information-guided denoising diffusion probabilistic model for fault diagnosis with imbalanced data - ScienceDirect\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6810a6a3fa386e7e\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0952197625003124\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3fc158a242ad1033\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nIn particular, out-of-distribution (OOD) detection is susceptible to interference from the overlap between training data distribution and the features of unknown samples, resulting in degraded diagnostic performance. To overcome this limitation, we propose a novel bearing fault diagnosis method that designs a conditional diffusion model to detect bearing faults by exploiting differential OOD error.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3fc158a242ad1033\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"February 27, 2025\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.sciencedirect.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"dae3c028878b9c6c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nFault Diagnosis of Bearings based on a Dual-Path Transformer-based ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"dae3c028878b9c6c\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://link.springer.com/10.1007/s13369-025-10733-6\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d0adaa913da8b5f5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nExtensive experiments on three benchmark datasets under extreme imbalance conditions demonstrate that DTAMNet significantly outperforms state-of-the-art methods, achieving average accuracies of 80.57%, 83.50%, and 84.38% under severe imbalance ratios of 0.05, substantially exceeding comparative methods that ranged from 14.29% to 76.48%. Ablation studies confirm the effectiveness of each proposed component.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d0adaa913da8b5f5\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"October 15, 2025\",\n      \"siteName\": \"link.springer.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0d745d3a81f2f2df\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nDifferential out-of-distribution error guidance for unknown bearing fault diagnosis with conditional diffusion model - ScienceDirect\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0d745d3a81f2f2df\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0952197625013521\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"07334378be982512\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nIn particular, out-of-distribution (OOD) detection is susceptible to interference from the overlap between training data distribution and the features of unknown samples, resulting in degraded diagnostic performance. To overcome this limitation, we propose a novel bearing fault diagnosis method that designs a conditional diffusion model to detect bearing faults by exploiting differential OOD error.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"07334378be982512\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"June 18, 2025\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.sciencedirect.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"226a753ba691a81e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGitHub - CHAOZHAO-1/DG-PHM: This is a reposotory that includes paper、code and datasets about domain generalization-based fault diagnosis and prognosis. (基于领域泛化的故障诊断和预测)\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"226a753ba691a81e\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/CHAOZHAO-1/DG-PHM\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c92fdfecea86e242\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAdversarial-Causal Representation Learning Networks for Machine fault diagnosis under unseen conditions based on vibration and acoustic signals [EAAI 2024] A novel hybrid data-driven domain generalization approach with dual-perspective feature fusion for intelligent fault diagnosis [EAAI 2024] Bearing fault diagnostic framework under unknown working conditions based on condition-guided diffusion model [Measurement 2024]\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c92fdfecea86e242\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"DP-CDDPM-AC dual path conditional diffusion fault diagnosis","provider":"brave","count":5,"tookMs":1414,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"brave","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"abfa9174dd07450c\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nA fault diagnosis method based on an improved diffusion model under limited sample conditions | PLOS One\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"abfa9174dd07450c\">>>","url":"https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0309714","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2944e72201b525fa\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nIn the process of inverse diffusion, if we give xt and x0, we can calculate xt-1 based on the posterior diffusion conditional probability. (7) According to the properties of the Gaussian distribution and Formula (1), it can be concluded that (8)\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2944e72201b525fa\">>>","published":"September 3, 2024","siteName":"journals.plos.org"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6810a6a3fa386e7e\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nA global information-guided denoising diffusion probabilistic model for fault diagnosis with imbalanced data - ScienceDirect\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6810a6a3fa386e7e\">>>","url":"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0952197625003124","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3fc158a242ad1033\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nIn particular, out-of-distribution (OOD) detection is susceptible to interference from the overlap between training data distribution and the features of unknown samples, resulting in degraded diagnostic performance. To overcome this limitation, we propose a novel bearing fault diagnosis method that designs a conditional diffusion model to detect bearing faults by exploiting differential OOD error.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3fc158a242ad1033\">>>","published":"February 27, 2025","siteName":"www.sciencedirect.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"dae3c028878b9c6c\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nFault Diagnosis of Bearings based on a Dual-Path Transformer-based ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"dae3c028878b9c6c\">>>","url":"https://link.springer.com/10.1007/s13369-025-10733-6","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d0adaa913da8b5f5\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nExtensive experiments on three benchmark datasets under extreme imbalance conditions demonstrate that DTAMNet significantly outperforms state-of-the-art methods, achieving average accuracies of 80.57%, 83.50%, and 84.38% under severe imbalance ratios of 0.05, substantially exceeding comparative methods that ranged from 14.29% to 76.48%. Ablation studies confirm the effectiveness of each proposed component.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d0adaa913da8b5f5\">>>","published":"October 15, 2025","siteName":"link.springer.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0d745d3a81f2f2df\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nDifferential out-of-distribution error guidance for unknown bearing fault diagnosis with conditional diffusion model - ScienceDirect\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0d745d3a81f2f2df\">>>","url":"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0952197625013521","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"07334378be982512\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nIn particular, out-of-distribution (OOD) detection is susceptible to interference from the overlap between training data distribution and the features of unknown samples, resulting in degraded diagnostic performance. To overcome this limitation, we propose a novel bearing fault diagnosis method that designs a conditional diffusion model to detect bearing faults by exploiting differential OOD error.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"07334378be982512\">>>","published":"June 18, 2025","siteName":"www.sciencedirect.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"226a753ba691a81e\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nGitHub - CHAOZHAO-1/DG-PHM: This is a reposotory that includes paper、code and datasets about domain generalization-based fault diagnosis and prognosis. (基于领域泛化的故障诊断和预测)\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"226a753ba691a81e\">>>","url":"https://github.com/CHAOZHAO-1/DG-PHM","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c92fdfecea86e242\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nAdversarial-Causal Representation Learning Networks for Machine fault diagnosis under unseen conditions based on vibration and acoustic signals [EAAI 2024] A novel hybrid data-driven domain generalization approach with dual-perspective feature fusion for intelligent fault diagnosis [EAAI 2024] Bearing fault diagnostic framework under unknown working conditions based on condition-guided diffusion model [Measurement 2024]\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c92fdfecea86e242\">>>","siteName":"github.com"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773721346074}}
