{"type":"message","id":"7df0f165","parentId":"18c3a6ba","timestamp":"2026-03-17T07:59:31.880Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f2a54875159449dd98a78ed3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# LaTeX 格式审查报告 (Round 4)\n\n## 审查结论：REVISE\n\n## 1. 编译状态\n\n| 项目 | 状态 |\n|------|------|\n| pdflatex 编译 | ✅ 成功 |\n| 输出页数 | 17 页 |\n| PDF 大小 | 257,181 bytes |\n| Error | ❌ 无 |\n\n## 2. Warning 检查\n\n### 2.1 严重 Warning\n无\n\n### 2.2 排版 Warning (Overfull/Underfull)\n共 23 处 Overfull/Underfull hbox/vbox 警告，主要原因：\n- 段落行间距不当\n- 公式或长单词导致行溢出\n\n**示例：**\n- `Overfull \\hbox (272.8617pt too wide)` - methodology.tex 第 52 行\n- `Overfull \\hbox (77.09819pt too wide)` - methodology.tex 第 123 行\n\n**说明：** 这些是 LaTeX 常见的排版警告，不影响编译和阅读，但影响文档美观度。\n\n### 2.3 Font 警告\n多处字体替代警告（如 `Font shape 'OT1/ptm/bx/n' not available, Font shape 'OT1/ptm/b/n' tried instead`）。这是常见问题，不影响功能。\n\n## 3. 图片/表格引用检查\n\n### ❌ 严重问题：图表引用不正确\n\n全文使用 \"The figure\" / \"The table\" 这样的文字引用，而不是使用 `\\ref{}` 进行正确的 LaTeX 引用。\n\n**问题位置（部分）：**\n- `experiments.tex:38` - \"The figure\" \n- `experiments.tex:22` - \"The table\"\n- `experiments.tex:89` - \"The table\"\n- `experiments.tex:100` - \"As shown in The table\"\n- `methodology.tex:23` - \"The table\"\n- `methodology.tex:55` - \"The figure\"\n- `methodology.tex:74` - \"The figure\"\n- `methodology.tex:112` - \"The figure\"\n\n**正确引用方式应为：**\n```latex\n如图~\\ref{fig:xxx} 所示\n如表~\\ref{tab:xxx} 所示\n```\n\n### ⚠️ 图表未插入正文\n\n虽然 `figures/` 目录下有 6 张图片 (figure_1.png ~ figure_6.png)，但在正文中未找到：\n- `\\includegraphics{}` 命令\n- `figure` 环境\n- `table` 环境\n\n## 4. 参考文献引用检查\n\n### ✅ 参考文献状态正常\n\n- `paper.bbl` 正确生成\n- 包含 13 条参考文献\n- 引用格式正确（使用 `\\cite{}`）\n- 编译无警告\n\n**引用的文献：**\n- lampert2009, feng2020, chen2021, hu2022, xing2022, song2025\n- lv2021, zhuo2022\n- ho2020, guo2023, wang2024\n- radford2021clip, wang2025\n\n## 5. 修复要求\n\n### 🔴 必须修复\n\n1. **图表引用规范化**\n   - 将所有 \"The figure\" / \"The table\" 替换为 `\\ref{}` 引用\n   - 添加 figure/table 环境和 `\\label{}` 标签\n   \n   示例：\n   ```latex\n   % 原文\n   The figure illustrates...\n   \n   % 修改为\n  如图~\\ref{fig:architecture} 所示...\n   \n   \\begin{figure}[htbp]\n   \\centering\n   \\includegraphics[width=0.8\\linewidth]{figure_1.png}\n   \\caption{System Architecture}\n   \\label{fig:architecture}\n   \\end{figure}\n   ```\n\n2. **插入缺失的图表**\n   - 使用 `\\includegraphics{}` 插入 6 张图片\n   - 为每张图片添加 caption 和 label\n   - 创建表格环境插入 3 个表格\n\n### 🟡 建议修复\n\n3. **Overfull 警告**\n   - 调整 methodology.tex 第 52 行和第 123 行的公式/段落\n   - 使用 `\\allowbreak` 或手动断行\n\n## 6. 总结\n\n| 检查项 | 状态 |\n|--------|------|\n| 编译无 Error | ✅ |\n| 参考文献正确 | ✅ |\n| 图表引用正确 | ❌ |\n| 图表插入正文 | ❌ |\n\n**建议：** 需要返工修复图表引用和插入问题后再次审查。\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773734371875}}
{"type":"message","id":"80d5fb9b","parentId":"7df0f165","timestamp":"2026-03-17T07:59:46.082Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Reviewer 提出了新的问题：\n1. 图表引用使用文字而不是 \\ref{} 格式\n2. 图表未插入正文\n\n这是一个 REVISE 结果。根据流程，最多 3 轮，我已经到了第 4 轮。但用户要求继续，所以我需要修复这些问题。让我直接修复这些问题：\n1. 在 paper.tex 中添加 figure 和 table 环境\n2. 修正引用格式\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"⚠️ **Round 4 审查：REVISE**\n\n### 问题\n- ❌ 图表未插入正文\n- ❌ 引用格式使用文字而非 \\ref{}\n\n让我直接修复这些问题：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7660e72f9c0e4c6599c8dce7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"SHARED=\"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-4\"\n\n# 检查当前 paper.tex 内容\nhead -50 \"$SHARED/final/paper.tex\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"minimax/minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":994,"output":274,"cacheRead":152896,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":154164,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773734371884}}
{"type":"message","id":"acfa61d8","parentId":"80d5fb9b","timestamp":"2026-03-17T07:59:46.091Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_7660e72f9c0e4c6599c8dce7","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\\documentclass[12pt,journal]{IEEEtran}\n\\usepackage{graphicx}\n\\usepackage{amsmath}\n\\usepackage{amssymb}\n\\usepackage{cite}\n\\usepackage{balance}\n\n% 设置图表路径\n\\graphicspath{{../figures/}}\n\n\\begin{document}\n\n% 标题\n\\title{CLIP-Enhanced Semantic Manifold Diffusion for Zero-Shot Fault Diagnosis}\n\n% 作者\n\\author{Author Name,~Member,~IEEE\n\\thanks{Manuscript received Month Day, Year; revised Month Day, Year; accepted Month Day, Year. This work was supported by.}}\n%\\thanks{}}\n\n% 摘要\n\\begin{abstract}\nIndustrial fault diagnosis has emerged as a critical challenge in modern manufacturing systems. While deep learning methods have achieved remarkable success in controlled environments, they fundamentally rely on the ``closed-world\" assumption requiring abundant labeled training data for each fault class. This paper proposes CLIP-Enhanced Semantic Manifold Diffusion (CESM-Diff), a novel zero-shot fault diagnosis framework that leverages large-scale vision-language pre-training for semantic representation. Our approach introduces a dual-path diffusion mechanism that simultaneously processes physical signal features and semantic embeddings, coupled with a cross-path attention module for bidirectional interaction. Additionally, we propose a Semantic Manifold Interpolation (SMI) mechanism that enables topological reasoning for intermediate fault states. Extensive experiments on benchmark datasets demonstrate that CESM-Diff consistently outperforms state-of-the-art zero-shot learning methods, achieving significant improvements in harmonic mean and unseen class accuracy.\n\\end{abstract}\n\n% 关键词\n\\begin{IEEEkeywords}\nZero-shot fault diagnosis, diffusion model, CLIP, semantic manifold, industrial diagnostics.\n\\end{IEEEkeywords}\n\n% 正文\n\\maketitle\n\n\\input{../drafts/introduction}\n\\input{../drafts/related_work}\n\\input{../drafts/methodology}\n\\input{../drafts/experiments}\n\\input{../drafts/conclusion}\n\n% 参考文献\n\\bibliographystyle{plain}\n\\bibliography{../references/references}\n\n\\end{document}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3,"aggregated":"\\documentclass[12pt,journal]{IEEEtran}\n\\usepackage{graphicx}\n\\usepackage{amsmath}\n\\usepackage{amssymb}\n\\usepackage{cite}\n\\usepackage{balance}\n\n% 设置图表路径\n\\graphicspath{{../figures/}}\n\n\\begin{document}\n\n% 标题\n\\title{CLIP-Enhanced Semantic Manifold Diffusion for Zero-Shot Fault Diagnosis}\n\n% 作者\n\\author{Author Name,~Member,~IEEE\n\\thanks{Manuscript received Month Day, Year; revised Month Day, Year; accepted Month Day, Year. This work was supported by.}}\n%\\thanks{}}\n\n% 摘要\n\\begin{abstract}\nIndustrial fault diagnosis has emerged as a critical challenge in modern manufacturing systems. While deep learning methods have achieved remarkable success in controlled environments, they fundamentally rely on the ``closed-world\" assumption requiring abundant labeled training data for each fault class. This paper proposes CLIP-Enhanced Semantic Manifold Diffusion (CESM-Diff), a novel zero-shot fault diagnosis framework that leverages large-scale vision-language pre-training for semantic representation. Our approach introduces a dual-path diffusion mechanism that simultaneously processes physical signal features and semantic embeddings, coupled with a cross-path attention module for bidirectional interaction. Additionally, we propose a Semantic Manifold Interpolation (SMI) mechanism that enables topological reasoning for intermediate fault states. Extensive experiments on benchmark datasets demonstrate that CESM-Diff consistently outperforms state-of-the-art zero-shot learning methods, achieving significant improvements in harmonic mean and unseen class accuracy.\n\\end{abstract}\n\n% 关键词\n\\begin{IEEEkeywords}\nZero-shot fault diagnosis, diffusion model, CLIP, semantic manifold, industrial diagnostics.\n\\end{IEEEkeywords}\n\n% 正文\n\\maketitle\n\n\\input{../drafts/introduction}\n\\input{../drafts/related_work}\n\\input{../drafts/methodology}\n\\input{../drafts/experiments}\n\\input{../drafts/conclusion}\n\n% 参考文献\n\\bibliographystyle{plain}\n\\bibliography{../references/references}\n\n\\end{document}","cwd":"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/leader/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773734386087}}
